{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idee5c5d24-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s930"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"930"},"text":"§ 930.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Congressional declaration of policy","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"It is hereby declared to be the policy of the Congress that adequate funds should be made available to rural electric and telephone systems through direct, insured and guaranteed loans at interest rates which will allow them to achieve the objectives of the Rural Electrification Act of 1936, as amended [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s901"},"text":"7 U.S.C. 901","children":[],"tail":" et seq.], and that such rural electric and telephone systems should be encouraged and assisted to develop their resources and ability to achieve the financial strength needed to enable them to satisfy their credit needs from their own financial organizations and other sources at reasonable rates and terms consistent with the loan applicant’s ability to pay and achievement of the Act’s objectives."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idee5c5d25-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/32/s1"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–32, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-05-11"},"text":"May 11, 1973","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/87/65"},"text":"87 Stat. 65","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idee5c5d26-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idee5c5d27-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idee5c5d28-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Rural Electrification Act of 1936 and the Act, referred to in text, are ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1936-05-20/ch432"},"text":"act May 20, 1936, ch. 432","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/49/1363"},"text":"49 Stat. 1363","children":[],"tail":", which is classified generally to this chapter. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s901"},"text":"section 901 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idee5c5d29-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section is comprised of the first sentence of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/32/s1"},"text":"section 1 of Pub. L. 93–32","children":[],"tail":". The last sentence of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/32/s1"},"text":"section 1 of Pub. L. 93–32","children":[],"tail":" provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/93/32/s1"},"text":"“The Rural Electrification Act of 1936, as amended (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s901–950/b"},"text":"7 U.S.C. 901–950(b)","children":[],"tail":"), is therefore further amended as hereinafter provided.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was not enacted as part of the Rural Electrification Act of 1936 which comprises this chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idee5c5d2a-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDate","id":"idee5c5d2b-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/32/s12"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–32, § 12","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-05-14"},"text":"May 14, 1973","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/87/71"},"text":"87 Stat. 71","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/93/32/s12"},"text":"“This Act [enacting sections 906a, 930, and 933 to 940 of this title, amending sections 903, 931, 932, 945, 946, 947, and 948 of this title, and enacting provisions set out as notes under this section] shall take effect upon enactment [","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-05-11"},"text":"May 11, 1973","children":[],"tail":"].”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idee5c5d2c-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Reservation of Right To Repeal, Alter, or Amend ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/32"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–32","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/32/s11"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–32, § 11","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-05-14"},"text":"May 14, 1973","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/87/71"},"text":"87 Stat. 71","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/93/32/s11"},"text":"“The right to repeal, alter, or amend, this Act [enacting sections 906a, 930, and 933 to 940 of this title, amending sections 903, 931, 932, 945, 946, 947, and 948 of this title, and enacting provisions set out as notes under this section] is expressly reserved.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
